			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><h2><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/The_Difference_Between_Living_and_Existing.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-1414 alignright" title="The Difference Between Living and Existing" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/The_Difference_Between_Living_and_Existing.jpg" alt="The Difference Between Living and Existing" width="218" height="304" /></a></h2>
<p><em>Preparing for the Zombie Apocalypse. Kimanzi Constable joins us to explain what it means to truly live. 9 steps towards radical change.</em></p>
<h2>Speaking of “Just Existing”&#8230;</h2>
<p>You don’t want to be a zombie in your life, but you also don’t want zombies to end your life! That’s why we’re glad the CDC provided this helpful <a title="Preparedness 101: Zombie Pandemic" href="http://www.cdc.gov/phpr/zombies.htm">Preparedness 101: Zombie Apocalypse</a>.</p>
<h2>9 Steps Between Just Existing and Truly Living</h2>
<p>Special guest, author and speaker Kimanzi Constable joins us on the show. For the last 10 years Kimanzi has owned a vacation service for independent operators. At its height, the company brought in <strong>$200,000</strong> and had <strong>5 employees</strong>. Kimanzi now works for one independent operator, maintains a website blog, and is a noted author and speaker.</p>
<p>His first book was <em><a href="http://www.amazon.com/Tales-Everyday-Workingman-Woman-ebook/dp/B005GXS35A">Tales of the Everyday Working Man</a></em>. Today he shares with us some lessons from his latest book, <em><a href="http://www.amazon.com/Difference-Between-Living-Existing-ebook/dp/B007EDMT32">The Difference Between Living and Existing: A Nine Month Plan To Radically Change Your Life</a></em>.</p>
<p>Check out his website, <a href="http://talesofwork.com/blog/">Tales of Work</a>, for information about his books and speaking schedule, and follow him on Twitter at <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/kimanzic">@kimanzic</a>.</p>
<p>In our conversation today, Kimanzi takes us through an overview of his nine-month plan to bring radical change to your life:</p>
<ul>
<li>Month 1: Figure out what.</li>
<li>Month 2: Take small steps.</li>
<li>Month 3: Plan an outline for Point A to Point B.</li>
<li>Month 4: Figure out your finances.</li>
<li>Month 5: Get rid of anything negative in your life.</li>
<li>Month 6: Finalize the plans and start execution.</li>
<li>Month 7: Put your toes in the water; do a trial to confirm this is really what you want.</li>
<li>Month 8: Actually do it!</li>
<li>Month 9: Give back.</li>
</ul>
