		<itunes:summary>Preparing for the Zombie Apocalypse. Kimanzi Constable joins us to explain what it means to truly live. 9 steps towards radical change.
Speaking of “Just Existing”...
You don’t want to be a zombie in your life, but you also don’t want zombies to end your life! That’s why we’re glad the CDC provided this helpful Preparedness 101: Zombie Apocalypse.
9 Steps Between Just Existing and Truly Living
Special guest, author and speaker Kimanzi Constable joins us on the show. For the last 10 years Kimanzi has owned a vacation service for independent operators. At its height, the company brought in $200,000 and had 5 employees. Kimanzi now works for one independent operator, maintains a website blog, and is a noted author and speaker.

His first book was Tales of the Everyday Working Man. Today he shares with us some lessons from his latest book, The Difference Between Living and Existing: A Nine Month Plan To Radically Change Your Life.

Check out his website, Tales of Work, for information about his books and speaking schedule, and follow him on Twitter at @kimanzic.

In our conversation today, Kimanzi takes us through an overview of his nine-month plan to bring radical change to your life:

	Month 1: Figure out what.
	Month 2: Take small steps.
	Month 3: Plan an outline for Point A to Point B.
	Month 4: Figure out your finances.
	Month 5: Get rid of anything negative in your life.
	Month 6: Finalize the plans and start execution.
	Month 7: Put your toes in the water; do a trial to confirm this is really what you want.
	Month 8: Actually do it!
	Month 9: Give back.</itunes:summary>
