		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=1336</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[There is no “I” in TEAM, but there are 5 “I’s” in LEADERSHIP. Are life plans crap? Looking forward to Michael Hyatt’s new book, Platform. Jesse invites into Man Cave One our special guest Cody Gascho, the lead guy at Praxis Church. There is no “I” in TEAM, but there are 5 “I’s” in LEADERSHIP Listening [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><em><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Cody_Gascho.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-1348" title="Cody Gascho helps answer the question, &quot;Are life plans crap?&quot;" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Cody_Gascho-300x225.jpg" alt="Cody Gascho helps answer the question, &quot;Are life plans crap?&quot;" width="300" height="225" /></a>There is no “I” in TEAM, but there are 5 “I’s” in LEADERSHIP. Are life plans crap? Looking forward to Michael Hyatt’s new book, Platform.</em></p>
<p>Jesse invites into Man Cave One our special guest <a href="http://twitter.com/codygascho">Cody Gascho</a>, the lead guy at <a href="http://createpraxis.com">Praxis Church</a>.</p>
<h2>There is no “I” in TEAM, but there are 5 “I’s” in LEADERSHIP</h2>
<p>Listening to Michael Hyatt’s <em>This Is Your Life</em> podcast earlier this week about the &#8220;<a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/012-the-5-marks-of-authentic-leadership-podcast.html">5 Marks of Authentic Leadership</a>,&#8221; Jesse was struck by the fact that Cody exemplified these five marks, seemingly without trying. For a directing, extroverted guy like Jesse, Cody seems like a quiet, non-leading sort of guy… and yet a large number of people in the Ausable River Valley are following his leadership.</p>
<p>Jesse noted that Michael suggested that authentic leaders should pursue all five of these “I” characteristics:</p>
<ul>
<li>Authentic leaders have <strong>insight</strong>.</li>
<li>Authentic leaders demonstrate<strong> initiative</strong>.</li>
<li>Authentic leaders exert <strong>influence</strong>.</li>
<li>Authentic leaders have <strong>impact</strong>.</li>
<li>Authentic leaders exercise <strong>integrity</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Are life plans crap?</h2>
<p>Coincidentally, Cody is the guy who introduced us to Michael Hyatt about two years ago. And in early 2011, Jesse, JJ, and Cody decided to meet on a regular basis to walk through Michael’s ebook, <em><a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/life-plan">Creating Your Personal Life Plan</a></em> (available free for those who sign up for Michael’s free newsletter).</p>
<p>Of the three guys, Jesse has been the most proactive in completing and following the life planning process (he’s always been an overachiever). Sadly, today marks one full year since Cody has last touched his life plan. And even Jesse hasn’t fully implemented the process. Does that mean life plans are crap?</p>
<p>Another leader who teaches similar principles but with different processes is Kent Julian. Many people will appreciate Kent’s approach to Goal Getting and Time Investment (those who sign up for his free newsletter can get his ebook <em><a href="http://www.liveitforward.com/">Goal Setting That Actually Works!</a></em> for free).</p>
<h2>Looking forward to Michael Hyatt’s new book</h2>
<p>We’re pleased that Jesse was invited to review an advance copy of Michael Hyatt’s new book, <em><a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/platform">Platform: Get Noticed in a Noisy World</a></em>. Today he finished reading the book, and he will share his thoughts on Man Cave Radio early the week of May 21. Stay tuned for your chance to receive $375.98 worth of free bonus content.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><em>Note: We receive no compensation or commissions from Michael Hyatt or Kent Julian.</em></p>
<p><strong id="internal-source-marker_0.11279066163115203"> Have you tried these or other life planning approaches? What has your experience been? Are they helpful or crap?</strong></p>
