			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><em><strong><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Avengers.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1277" style="margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" title="Avengers" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Avengers-300x168.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="168" /></a></strong><strong>**SPOILER ALERT** Don&#8217;t listen if you haven&#8217;t seen the movie yet.</strong></em> When the Demi-God Loki threatens the earth with an alien army, Nick Fury, Director of the international peacekeeping agency known as S.H.I.E.L.D., brings together a team of superheroes to save the planet. All your favorite heroes – from Iron Man to Captain America – assemble as a mighty team: The Avengers.  Starring Robert Downey Jr., Chris Evans, Mark Ruffalo, Chris Hemsworth, Scarlett Johansson, Jeremy Renner and Samuel L. Jackson, and directed by Joss Whedon.</p>
<p>This podcast is longer than our usual Man Cave Movie discussion, but that&#8217;s simply because The Avengers has so many interesting things to talk about. What do you expect from the first movie in years to give Titanic and Avatar a run for the money?<strong> For more on The Avengers, check out our other discussions of this series!</strong></p>
