		<item>
		<title>MCR 026: I Can’t Stop Working (Part 2)</title>
		<link>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-026-i-cant-stop-working-part-2/</link>
		<comments>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-026-i-cant-stop-working-part-2/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 03 May 2012 17:21:17 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cave@mancaveradio.com (Jesse and J. J. Lahey)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[business success]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Winning at Work]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=1219</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Age-Activated Attention-Deficit Disorder. I Can’t Stop Working: 4 Ways to Manage How Much You Work (Part 2). Hootcha! Age-Activated Attention-Deficit Disorder AAADD is a serious disorder that we believe is caused by multi-tasking. We know it’s serious because we learned about it from the Car Talk guys. I Can’t Stop Working: 4 Ways to Manage [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><em><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Over-worked_man_removing_tie.jpg"><img class="alignright  wp-image-1230" title="Overworked man removing tie." src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Over-worked_man_removing_tie.jpg" alt="Overworked man removing tie." width="237" height="322" /></a>Age-Activated Attention-Deficit Disorder. I Can’t Stop Working: 4 Ways to Manage How Much You Work (Part 2). Hootcha!</em></p>
<h2><em></em>Age-Activated Attention-Deficit Disorder</h2>
<p>AAADD is a serious disorder that we believe is caused by multi-tasking. We know it’s serious because we learned about it from the <a href="http://www.cartalk.com/content/age-activated-attention-deficit-disorder-how-it-goes">Car Talk guys</a>.</p>
<h2>I Can’t Stop Working: 4 Ways to Manage How Much You Work (Part 2)</h2>
<p>Based on what’s been helpful to him, Jesse shares four suggestions to manage how much you work.</p>
<p><strong><em>1. Understand the importance of your other priorities.</em></strong></p>
<p>Michael Hyatt does a great job discussing the why and how of managing your priorities in his podcast <em>This Is Your Life</em> episode 009, &#8220;<a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/009-is-work-life-balance-really-possible-podcast.html">Is Work-Life Balance Really Possible?</a>&#8221;</p>
<p>In his book <em><a href="http://www.amazon.com/When-Work-Family-Collide-Cheating/dp/1601423799">When Work and Family Collide</a></em>, Andy Stanley says that for anyone who has spouse and kids, family “is your only unique responsibility. On the marketplace side of the equation, you’re expendable. Even if you own your own company, you’re expendable. You know that.”</p>
<p><strong><em>2. Have a designated time and place for work.</em></strong></p>
<p>A great resource to help you set boundaries for your work is Dr. Henry Cloud’s book, <em><a href="http://www.amazon.com/The-One-Life-Solution-Achieving-Professional/dp/B0064XF1Y2/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1335450920&amp;sr=1-1">The One-Life Solution: Reclaim Your Personal Life While Achieving Greater Professional Success</a>.</em><strong><strong></strong></strong></p>
<p><strong><em>3. Understand what&#8217;s behind your drive to work so much.</em><strong><br />
</strong></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Is it your own fears? Trust problem? Cultural validation? Fear of missing an opportunity? I only matter when….</li>
<li>Is it the culture of your company or team? Your boss? (Jesse&#8217;s story of first job out of school)</li>
<li>Is it a specific season of life or of the year? Breadwinner? (Healthy tension)</li>
<li>Are you just working from prior programming / work habits?</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><em>4. Make the most of the time you do spend working.</em><strong><br />
</strong></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Choose work that you&#8217;re passionate about.</li>
<li>Play to your strengths. Choose work that allows you to spend 80% of the time in a good fit with the way you are wired. (For example, Jesse most enjoys creative work and interacting with other people, with about a 50/50 split on solo work vs. team work. He is good at detailed and management work too, but if that consumes the majority of his work time, he gets burned out.)</li>
<li>Delegate anything that someone else could do better or cheaper than you, or at least roughly as good as you.</li>
<li>Remember the Pareto (80/20) principle so that you are focusing 80% of your time on what produces the most important results. Focus on results that matter, not just achievement or (even worse) activity.</li>
<li>Beware of multi-tasking. Focus on one thing at a time, for maximum productivity and work satisfaction. See <a title="How (and Why) to Stop Multitasking" href="http://blogs.hbr.org/bregman/2010/05/how-and-why-to-stop-multitaski.html">How (and Why) to Stop Multitasking</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong id="internal-source-marker_0.8191046244464815">Hootcha!</strong></h2>
<p>It’s not easy keeping up with teenage kids, but that doesn’t stop Jesse from trying.</p>
<div class="shr-publisher-1219"></div><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><div class='shareaholic-like-buttonset' style='float:none;height:30px;'><a class='shareaholic-fblike' data-shr_layout='button_count' data-shr_showfaces='false' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fmcr-026-i-cant-stop-working-part-2%2F' data-shr_title='MCR+026%3A+I+Can%E2%80%99t+Stop+Working+%28Part+2%29'></a><a class='shareaholic-googleplusone' data-shr_size='medium' data-shr_count='true' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fmcr-026-i-cant-stop-working-part-2%2F' data-shr_title='MCR+026%3A+I+Can%E2%80%99t+Stop+Working+%28Part+2%29'></a><a class='shareaholic-tweetbutton' data-shr_count='horizontal' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fmcr-026-i-cant-stop-working-part-2%2F' data-shr_title='MCR+026%3A+I+Can%E2%80%99t+Stop+Working+%28Part+2%29'></a></div><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?a=Cbv4BcA6WTc:Hu_rdtMvDQU:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?a=Cbv4BcA6WTc:Hu_rdtMvDQU:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></img></a>
