		<title>MCR-024: The Tyranny of the Urgent</title>
		<link>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-024-the-tyranny-of-the-urgent/</link>
		<comments>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-024-the-tyranny-of-the-urgent/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 19 Apr 2012 23:10:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cave@mancaveradio.com (Jesse and J. J. Lahey)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=1040</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Count-down “The Avengers.” “Mission: Impossible &#8211; Ghost Protocol” comes to DVD and iTunes. Fighting the good fight against email. Important vs. Urgent. Countdown to The Avengers With the impending May 4th release of the much-anticipated blockbuster The Avengers, Jesse and J. J. take some time to review and analyze the previous five movies in Marvel’s [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><em><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/The_Avengers.jpg"><img class="alignright  wp-image-1045" title="The Avengers" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/The_Avengers.jpg" alt="The Avengers" width="308" height="210" /></a>Count-down “The Avengers.” <em>“</em>Mission: Impossible &#8211; Ghost Protocol<em>”</em> comes to DVD and iTunes. Fighting the good fight against email. Important vs. Urgent.</em></p>
<h2 dir="ltr">Countdown to The Avengers</h2>
<p>With the impending May 4th release of the much-anticipated blockbuster The Avengers, Jesse and J. J. take some time to review and analyze the previous five movies in Marvel’s stellar superhero universe.</p>
<p>The guys will review one movie each week until <em>The Avengers</em> is released. Their <a title="Movie Review: “The Incredible Hulk”" href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/movie-review-the-incredible-hulk/">review of <em>The Incredible Hulk</em></a> is already up, but stay tuned for upcoming reviews of <em>Iron Man &amp; Iron Man 2</em>, <em>Thor</em>, and <em>Captain America</em>.</p>
<p><strong>Update: </strong>For more, listen to <a title="Movie Review: “Iron Man”" href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/movie-review-ironman/">Jesse and J. J.&#8217;s  review of <em>Iron Man</em> here</a>.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">Mission: Impossible 4</h2>
<p>The latest <em>Mission: Impossible</em> movie, <em>Ghost Protocol</em>, finally gets a physical release (and digital, if that’s more your style). <a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/mission-impossible-ghost-protocol/">The guys loved <em>Ghost Protocol</em> when they reviewed it</a> in January, and the review has been our most-downloaded show to date.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">Reader Comments</h2>
<p>On <a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-022-the-first-90-days-of-the-rest-of-your-life/">the blog post for episode 22</a>, commenter Christopher finds that breaking the year up into quarters, goal-wise, works better for him. Darrel responds to Jesse via Twitter, asking if he’s had the courage to simply delete backlogged emails in his own inbox, as recommended in Mark Hurst’s book, <em><a href="http://www.amazon.com/Bit-Literacy-Productivity-Information-Overload/dp/0979368103/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1334872545&amp;sr=8-1">Bit Literacy</a></em>.</p>
<p>Jesse talks about a presentation called &#8220;<a title="Inbox Zero by Merlin Mann" href="http://youtu.be/z9UjeTMb3Yk">Inbox Zero</a>&#8221; by Merlin Mann, a well-known speaker, writer, and podcaster (his most well-known podcast being <em><a title="Back to Work" href="http://5by5.tv/b2w">Back to Work</a></em>). Mann gives moving presentations wherever he goes, including his speech &#8220;<a href="http://youtu.be/Lk0hSeQ5s_k" target="_blank">Scared —less: How I (Mostly) Learned to Love Being Afraid of Pretty Much Everything</a>&#8221; (note: contains swearing).</p>
<p>Receiving upwards of 100 emails per day, Jesse takes some cues from Michael Hyatt’s podcast episode “<a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/005-how-to-take-control-of-your-e-mail-inbox-podcast.html">How to Take Control of Your Email Inbox</a>” in order to shape his email habits.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">Important vs. Urgent</h2>
<p>The guys discuss the idea of separating things that are important from those that are simply urgent. Lots of things can be urgent, but very few of those things are actually<em> important</em>. Jesse talks about how to tell the difference between the two, and what to do if something falls into one category or the other, or both.</p>
