		<item>
		<title>MCR-020: Take the “Enjoy Now!” and “Do the Opposite” Approach</title>
		<link>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-020-enjoy-now-and-do-the-opposite/</link>
		<comments>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-020-enjoy-now-and-do-the-opposite/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 15 Mar 2012 20:46:55 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cave@mancaveradio.com (Jesse and J. J. Lahey)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=853</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[How contentment plays a huge part in your personal success. Enjoying the now. Going against the grain to achieve your goals. Holding the stars in the palm of your hand. Enjoy Now Ryan Eggenberger commented on &#8220;MCR 019: Sometimes Renting Is Better Than Owning.&#8221; “I rent an apartment and definitely love the freedom it is [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><em><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/different.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-860" title="Do the opposite." src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/different.jpg" alt="Do the opposite." width="285" height="213" /></a>How contentment plays a huge part in your personal success. Enjoying the now. Going against the grain to achieve your goals. Holding the stars in the palm of your hand.</em></p>
<h2>Enjoy Now</h2>
<p><a href="http://www.ryaneggenberger.com/">Ryan Eggenberger</a> commented on &#8220;<a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-019-sometimes-renting-is-better-than-owning/">MCR 019: Sometimes Renting Is Better Than Owning</a>.&#8221;</p>
<blockquote><p><em>“I rent an apartment and definitely love the freedom it is currently providing me.”</em></p></blockquote>
<p><a href="http://www.findingforwardmotion.com/">Tony Elam</a> commented on &#8220;<a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/7-reasons-being-debt-free-wont-make-you-happy">7 Reasons Being Debt-Free Won&#8217;t Make You Happy</a>.&#8221;</p>
<blockquote><p><em>“I love being debt free, but you are right it didn&#8217;t make us happy. I learned to be content way before I become debt free.”</em></p></blockquote>
<p>Tony’s comment prompted Jesse and J. J. to discuss how contentment makes a big difference in work and personal success and satisfaction. As Gretchen Rubin pointed out in The Happiness Project, <a href="http://www.happiness-project.com/happiness_project/2009/03/happiness-myth-no-8-youll-be-happy-as-soon-as-you.html">it helps tremendously to “Enjoy Now”</a> rather than getting tricked into the “arrival fallacy,” the belief that when you arrive at a certain destination, you’ll be happy.</p>
<p>Jesse and J. J. talk about how their focus on “Enjoying Now” was a big reason why their recent trip to Miami was such a blast. Their keys for getting the most satisfaction out of experiences like that are:<strong><strong><br />
</strong></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Enjoy and talk about the anticipation and preparation (“We’re going to have a great time! I’m already having fun just getting ready for it.”)</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Enjoy and talk about the experience while it’s happening (“Isn’t this great? Wow, look at that view!”)</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Enjoy and talk about experience (“Man, that was such a blast!”)</li>
</ul>
<p>And this isn’t just hype. As noted in <a href="http://www.happiness-project.com/">The Happiness Project</a>, studies show that talking with others like this truly does boost your happiness and satisfaction.</p>
<h2>Do the Opposite</h2>
<p>Speaker and author Kent Julian is often asked questions about the secret to success, such as:</p>
<p><em>“How can I achieve success in the most important roles of my life such as personal development, family, and work?”</em></p>
<p>Kent says the simple answer is … Just do the opposite of what 90% of the people are doing, and you’ll likely be very successful. <a href="http://www.liveitforward.com/secret-to-success-do-the-opposite/">Kent recently shared nine examples</a> of things you could do that are the opposite of what most people do. Jesse and J. J. discuss six of these and how they put them into practice:<strong><strong><br />
</strong></strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Wake up earlier than most.</li>
<li>Commit to reading 30-60 minutes everyday.</li>
<li>Exercise daily.</li>
<li>Be 100 percent responsible for your actions and attitudes throughout the day.</li>
<li>Invest your best effort at work.</li>
<li>Choose to see the glass half-full instead of half-empty.</li>
</ol>
<h2>Man Toys</h2>
<p>For all of the astronomy nuts out there, or just those looking to learn a little more about the celestial bodies above us, this week’s Man Toys are two smartphone apps, <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.google.android.stardroid&amp;hl=en">Sky Map</a> (for Android devices) and <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/app/planets/id305793334?mt=8">Planets</a> (for iOS devices), both completely free.</p>
