		<title>MCR-019: Sometimes Renting Is Better Than Owning</title>
		<link>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-019-sometimes-renting-is-better-than-owning/</link>
		<comments>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-019-sometimes-renting-is-better-than-owning/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 09 Mar 2012 18:09:08 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cave@mancaveradio.com (Jesse and J. J. Lahey)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=829</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Recorded from the “Mobile Man Cave” (a.k.a. Jesse’s car) in Miami, Florida, the guys reflect on life lessons from their trip to the Miami Beach half-marathon. J. J., Jesse, and Jesse’s dad Marty took a road trip to Miami and Key Largo for this event, which turned out to be their hardest running event yet. [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/2_.jpg"><img class="alignright  wp-image-834" title="Jesse running half marathon." src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/2_.jpg" alt="Jesse running half marathon." width="303" height="245" /></a>Recorded from the “Mobile Man Cave” (a.k.a. Jesse’s car) in Miami, Florida, the guys reflect on life lessons from their trip to the Miami Beach half-marathon.</p>
<p>J. J., Jesse, and Jesse’s dad Marty took a road trip to Miami and Key Largo for this event, which turned out to be their hardest running event yet. The scenery was beautiful and the people were fun, but the course was hilly and became quite hot as the morning went on. (See <a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/why-i-added-another-half-marathon-to-my-schedule/">Why I Added Another Half-Marathon to My Schedule</a>)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/1_.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-833 alignleft" title="Marty and J. J. in Florida." src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/1_.jpg" alt="Marty and J. J. in Florida." width="211" height="300" /></a>As we relaxed in Key Largo for a couple of days after our race, we realized a few lessons about truly enjoying life:</p>
<ul>
<li>Sometimes renting (or borrowing or just enjoying a friend’s item) is better than owning</li>
<li>Some experiences are most enjoyable simply due to their uniqueness or rarity</li>
<li>Some things are best enjoyed in their proper season</li>
</ul>
