		<itunes:subtitle>MCR 017: How Will the "Next Big Thing" Affect Your Work-Life Balance? 6 Ways to Have More Balance in Your (Love) Life. Man Toys: Bulletproof Polo Shirt &amp; Wild Man Beard Conditioner. The Next Big Thing. 6 Ways to Have More Balance in Your (Love) Life </itunes:subtitle>
		<itunes:summary>MCR 017: How Will the "Next Big Thing" Affect Your Work-Life Balance?
6 Ways to Have More Balance in Your (Love) Life. Man Toys: Bulletproof Polo Shirt &amp; Wild Man Beard Conditioner. The Next Big Thing.
6 Ways to Have More Balance in Your (Love) Life
Is your marriage in danger of being swallowed by “the maw of the mundane”? The problem is about balance, but not just work/life balance. Other priorities like kids, hobbies, friends, TV, Facebook — and yes, work — crowd out the time and energy you have for each other. Your wife no longer gets excited when you walk in the door. She’s no longer interested in your goals and dreams. She says “not tonight” too often.

After 17 years of marriage, Jesse has learned that if he makes Erin a top priority in his life, he’ll get the attention and priority from her that he desires. He shares six ways to keep more focus on your love life.

For more about this topic, including the links and resources discussed on the show, see Jesse’s blog post 6 Ways to Have More Balance in Your (Love) Life.
Man Toys
J. J. tells us about a wardrobe component that every guy needs: a bulletproof polo shirt.

And if you’re the type to let it all hang out, he suggests the Wild Man Beard Conditioner.

For more about these man toys, see J. J.’s blog post Man Toys: Bulletproof Polo Shirt &amp; Wild Man Beard Conditioner.
The Next Big Thing
Many people lose the balance in their life because they waste a lot of time and energy chasing the “next big thing.” Then that thing doesn’t turn out to be so big, so they’re soon chasing after another big thing.

Jesse discusses the “Fire Bullets, Then Cannonballs” principle from Great by Choice by Jim Collins. Great companies like Apple have used this approach in finding and launching big things like the iPod, iTunes, and iPhone. It’s a principle that guys can use to be successful -- and keep balance in both work and life.

For more about this topic, see Jesse’s blog post Fire Bullets First to Keep Balance in Life and Work.</itunes:summary>
