				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=595</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Immediately following Super Bowl 46, Jesse interviewed the SportsMan Ty Daniels and his brother Zach Lahey about the highlights of the game: the big plays, the quarterbacks Eli Manning vs. Tom Brady, the coaching &#8230; and yes, the commercials and Madonna&#8217;s half-time show. The New York Giants narrowly defeated the New England Patriots; while Doritos, [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/10526240-large.jpeg"><img class="alignright  wp-image-605" title="Bradshaw" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/10526240-large-300x296.jpg" alt="Giants running back Ahmad Bradshaw tackled by Patriots outside linebacker Brandon Spikes in 2nd quarter." width="210" height="207" /></a>Immediately following Super Bowl 46, Jesse interviewed the SportsMan Ty Daniels and his brother Zach Lahey about the highlights of the game: the big plays, the quarterbacks Eli Manning vs. Tom Brady, the coaching &#8230; and yes, the commercials and Madonna&#8217;s half-time show. The New York Giants narrowly defeated the New England Patriots; while Doritos, Fiatt, and Bridgestone crushed big boys Coke, Budweiser, and GE with memorable commercials.  It&#8217;s an all-football, all Super-Bowl, all SportsMan special edition of Man Cave Radio.</p>
