		<title>MCR-013: Burglar Mannequins &amp; 6 Steps to Beat Winter Blues</title>
		<link>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-013-burglar-mannequins/</link>
		<comments>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-013-burglar-mannequins/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 02 Feb 2012 15:16:44 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cave@mancaveradio.com (Jesse and J. J. Lahey)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=567</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Man Cave Radio episode 13 – Protecting your home with BurgleDolls. Six Steps to Beat the Winter Blues. Man Toy: CycleOps Bike Trainer. Winning At Work: What’s great about men, and how men need to change our approach to leadership in the 20th century. Interesting Guests. BurgleDolls Are you afraid of burglars? With the BurgleDoll, you don’t [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><em><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Criminal.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-571 alignright" title="Criminal" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Criminal.jpg" alt="Criminal" width="250" height="375" /></a>Man Cave Radio episode 13 – </em><em>Protecting your home with BurgleDolls. </em><em>Six Steps to Beat the Winter Blues. Man Toy: CycleOps Bike Trainer. Winning At Work: What’s great about men, and how men need to change our approach to leadership in the 20th century. Interesting Guests.</em></p>
<h2>BurgleDolls</h2>
<p>Are you afraid of burglars? With the BurgleDoll, you don’t have to worry about burglars ever again! With these life-size, burglar mannequins in your yard, potential thieves will think your house is already being robbed. (Use this product in addition to the BurgleStickers, which you paste on your window to make it look like there are bad guys in the house already.)</p>
<h2>Beating the Winter Blues</h2>
<p>Jesse was glad to read Michael Hyatt’s recent post, <a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/how-to-overcome-the-winter-blues.html" target="_blank">“How to Overcome the Winter Blues,”</a> in which Michael talked about how he overcame a mild winter-time depression. This is a topic that not many men talk about, but it’s pretty common. Over the last 3-4 winters, Jesse has experienced occasional periods of winter blues. Jesse comments on the four ways that Michael recommends for overcoming it, and adds two more keys that have helped him.</p>
<h2>Man Toy: CycleOps Indoor Bike Trainer</h2>
<p>The CycleOps indoor bike trainer provides a better experience than a stationery exercise bicyle, for a fraction of the cost. This device lets you bring your road bike indoors for the winter months.</p>
<p>Jesse welcomes Steve Hanley back to the Man Cave so both guys can give their take on the <a href="http://www.cycleops.com/" target="_blank">CycleOps</a> indoor bike trainer. They both recently started using the trainer to start preparing for the triathlons they&#8217;ve planned for the year. To see a video of Jesse demonstrating the trainer, visit <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XU5groEeCsA" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XU5groEeCsA</a></p>
<h2>Winning At Work &#8211; Part 1</h2>
<p>In the book<a href="http://mensanthology.com/about/" target="_blank"> Ordinary Men, Extraordinary Lives</a>, Roy Baumeister, Ph.D discusses some key differences between men and women (in general &#8212; there are many exceptions too). Men find their way to extremes. Men are more likely to accept risk, including taking on the dangerous jobs that our society needs people to do. Men may not be as good at close, one-on-one relationships, but they are very good at relating through large networks and groups.</p>
<h2>Interesting Guests</h2>
<p>We welcome three fascinating guests into Man Cave One: A mime, a man who speaks only the ends of words, and a man who looks like a dog.</p>
<h2>Winning At Work &#8211; Part 2</h2>
<p>Earlier in the show, we talked about some of the “man qualities” that have made a difference in world history and the workplace. However, we also need to recognize that the world has changed, and past styles of leadership and work don’t seem to be succeeding in the 21st century. Historically, men have excelled at a style of leadership that researchers at Burnham Rosen call Imperial (Stage 3) leadership &#8212; similar to a dictator or even a democratic president. Since the 1990s, however, the majority of successful leaders are practicing Interactive (Stage 4) leadership &#8212; more like a team coach. This style of leadership seems to come more naturally for many women &#8212; which is perhaps one reason why most leadership positions in corporate America are now filled by women (see <a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2010/07/the-end-of-men/8135/?single_page=true " target="_blank">“The End of Men”</a> in The Atlantic Monthly). However, the pendulum may have swung so far to the female side that we are in danger of seeing a lack of gender diversity in leadership that won&#8217;t be healthy for businesses, communities, and families. The world needs more men to become interactive leaders.</p>
<p>Note: <a href="http://www.burnhamrosen.com">Burnham Rosen</a> offers a three-day workshop on Interactive Leader. Jesse completed this workshop and highly recommends it.</p>
<p>For more on this subject, check out &#8220;<a title="Don’t Get Stuck at the Wrong Stage of Leadership" href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/dont-get-stuck-at-the-wrong-stage-of-leadership/">Don&#8217;t Get Stuck at the Wrong Stage of Leadership</a>.&#8221;</p>
<div class="shr-publisher-567"></div><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><div class='shareaholic-like-buttonset' style='float:none;height:30px;'><a class='shareaholic-fblike' data-shr_layout='button_count' data-shr_showfaces='false' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fmcr-013-burglar-mannequins%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-013%3A+Burglar+Mannequins+%26+6+Steps+to+Beat+Winter+Blues'></a><a class='shareaholic-googleplusone' data-shr_size='medium' data-shr_count='true' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fmcr-013-burglar-mannequins%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-013%3A+Burglar+Mannequins+%26+6+Steps+to+Beat+Winter+Blues'></a><a class='shareaholic-tweetbutton' data-shr_count='horizontal' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fmcr-013-burglar-mannequins%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-013%3A+Burglar+Mannequins+%26+6+Steps+to+Beat+Winter+Blues'></a></div><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div class="feedflare">
