		<dc:creator>cave@mancaveradio.com (Jesse and J. J. Lahey)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=487</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Endurance Events for Average Guys. Winning with Kids: The #1 Most Important Thing a Dad Can Do. SportsMan: Road to the Super Bowl. Man Heroes: Ordinary Men, Extraordinary Lives Endurance Events for Average Guys You may have been a jock in high school or even college, but when your school days ended, were you able [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><em><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/DrJimSharon.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-488" title="Dr. Jim Sharon" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/DrJimSharon.jpg" alt="Dr. Jim Sharon" width="162" height="207" /></a>Endurance Events for Average Guys. Winning with Kids: The #1 Most Important Thing a Dad Can Do. SportsMan: Road to the Super Bowl. </em><em>Man Heroes: Ordinary Men, Extraordinary Lives</em></p>
<h2><strong>Endurance Events for Average Guys</strong></h2>
<p>You may have been a jock in high school or even college, but when your school days ended, were you able to continue that sport as a life-long source of fun and fitness? Endurance events include runs such as 5ks and half-marathons; bicycle rides; and multi-sport events like triathlons and the Tough Mudder.</p>
<p>Steve Hanley explains why an average 30-something guy like him got interested in endurance events just two years ago – and now leads an <a href="http://fcaendurance.com/" target="_blank">FCA Endurance</a> group in Northwest Ohio.</p>
<p>Don’t miss next week’s show, as Jesse and Steve provide a review of their CycleOps bike trainers, an inexpensive and fun way to keep bicycling during the winter.</p>
<h2><strong>Winning with Kids: The #1 Most Important Thing a Dad Can Do</strong></h2>
<p>In his blog post &#8220;<a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/5-secrets-to-raising-kids-that-dont-drive-you-crazy/" target="_blank">5 Secrets to Raising Kids that Don’t Drive You Crazy</a>,&#8221; Jesse shared the five P.R.I.D.E. keys: Practice, Reinforcement, Insulate, Doing life together, and Enjoy.</p>
<p>Today, Jesse shares how the &#8220;Enjoy&#8221; key begins with a genuine smile. Smiling at your kids is such a simple thing, but many dads fail to provide their kids with this desperately needed sign of affection and affirmation.</p>
<h2><strong>SportsMan: Road to the Super Bowl</strong></h2>
<p>Ty Daniels explains how the New York Giants could make it to the Super Bowl despite a mediocre regular season. Who does he predict will win when the Giants face the New England Patriots in Super Bowl 46?</p>
<h2><strong>Man Heroes: Ordinary Men, Extraordinary Lives</strong></h2>
<p>We need to hear about Man Heroes this month!</p>
<p>In April, we will celebrate the 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary of the Titanic and its heroes who lived out “Women and Children First.” This month, however, more people are focused on the Jan. 13 tragedy of the cruise ship Costa Concordia near Italy. The ship’s captain, now nicknamed “Captain Coward,” is accused of causing a shipwreck (which resulted in at least 16 deaths) and then abandoning the ship before all passengers were evacuated. Some commentators have said the captain represents a modern stereotype of irresponsible, selfish, and perpetually adolescent men.</p>
<p>As a welcome contrast, our Man Hero this week is Steve Jones. Steve had a very difficult childhood, which included the alcoholism and suicide of his father. However, thanks to key mentors, this ordinary guy grew beyond his circumstances to live an extraordinary life – including playing football for the Seattle Seahawks, becoming a successful businessperson, and providing mentorship for others.</p>
<p>Steve’s story is shared with us by Dr. Jim Sharon, a clinical psychologist for more than 30 years. Readers can learn more about Steve Jones, as well as 39 other Man Heroes, in Dr. Sharon’s book <a href="http://mensanthology.com/about/" target="_blank"><em>Ordinary Men, Extraordinary Lives</em></a><em>. </em>Dr. Sharon is also the founder of the annual <a href="http://mensanthology.com/whole-man-expo/" target="_blank">Whole Man Expo</a>, an event that will be held on Sept. 8, 2012, to celebrate and support men <em>and</em> to increase public awareness of key challenges that contemporary men experience.</p>
<div class="shr-publisher-487"></div><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><div class='shareaholic-like-buttonset' style='float:none;height:30px;'><a class='shareaholic-fblike' data-shr_layout='button_count' data-shr_showfaces='false' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fmcr-012-ordinary-men-extraordinary-lives-featuring-dr-jim-sharon%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-012%3A+Ordinary+Men%2C+Extraordinary+Lives+%28featuring+Dr.+Jim+Sharon%29'></a><a class='shareaholic-googleplusone' data-shr_size='medium' data-shr_count='true' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fmcr-012-ordinary-men-extraordinary-lives-featuring-dr-jim-sharon%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-012%3A+Ordinary+Men%2C+Extraordinary+Lives+%28featuring+Dr.+Jim+Sharon%29'></a><a class='shareaholic-tweetbutton' data-shr_count='horizontal' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fmcr-012-ordinary-men-extraordinary-lives-featuring-dr-jim-sharon%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-012%3A+Ordinary+Men%2C+Extraordinary+Lives+%28featuring+Dr.+Jim+Sharon%29'></a></div><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?a=1YE9ZyVdH38:K_bkvj4VloA:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?a=1YE9ZyVdH38:K_bkvj4VloA:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></img></a>
