		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=478</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Winning with Kids Jesse shares how although most of his day went wrong, he made progress on one of his 90-day goals by doing something rather simple … taking his kids sledding. As shared in his blog post “5 Secrets to Raising Kids that Don’t Drive You Crazy,” Jesse and Erin have practiced the 5 [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><h2><strong><img class="alignright" title="Sledding off a jump" src="http://www.sxc.hu/pic/l/b/bj/bjearwicke/928447_76193309.jpg" alt="Sledding off a jump" width="187" height="219" />Winning with Kids</strong></h2>
<p>Jesse shares how although most of his day went wrong, he made progress on one of his 90-day goals by doing something rather simple … taking his kids sledding.</p>
<p>As shared in his blog post “<a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/5-secrets-to-raising-kids-that-dont-drive-you-crazy/" target="_blank">5 Secrets to Raising Kids that Don’t Drive You Crazy</a>,” Jesse and Erin have practiced the 5 PRIDE secrets for 16 years:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Practice:</strong> use short, fun training sessions to teach young children how to behave and respect authority</li>
<li><strong>Reinforcement:</strong> consistently reward attitudes and actions with appropriate rewards and consequences</li>
<li><strong>Insulate:</strong> filter out harmful influences as appropriate for their age, and teach them to protect themselves as they get older</li>
<li><strong>Doing Life Together: </strong>spend quality time in quantity, working and playing together</li>
<li><strong>Enjoy: </strong>smile at your children and have an attitude that builds connections with their heart</li>
</ul>
<p>Jesse says that taking the kids sledding was an example of “Doing Life Together.” He set a goal to create 12 memories for his kids this quarter, to help build strong relationships with them.</p>
<p>Jesse also encourages listeners to participate in a free teleseminar by Kent Julian on Feb. 2 called <a href="http://www.liveitforward.com/teleseminars/parent-it-forward-teleseminar/" target="_blank">“Parent It Forward &#8211; Parenting with Intentionality and Purpose.”</a></p>
<h2><strong>Jeep Sledding</strong></h2>
<p>Speaking of sledding, how about riding a sled pulled by a Jeep going 38 miles per hour? Zach Lahey says it’s all fun and games until the Jeep’s driver slams on the brakes.</p>
<h2><strong>Man Toys</strong></h2>
<p>J. J. and Jesse get geeked out over several items spotlighted in the February issue of <strong><a href="http://www.popularmechanics.com/" target="_blank">Popular Mechanics</a>:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://us.microplane.com/microplaneeasyprepmeattenderizer.aspx" target="_blank">Microplane’s Easy Prep Meat Tenderizer</a>: could also double as a weapon if you get attacked.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.popularmechanics.com/technology/gadgets/news/the-rise-of-the-ultrabook-ces-analysis-6636800?click=main_sr" target="_blank">Intel Ultrabooks</a>: HP, Ausus, Lenovo, and Dell are bring their answer to the MacBook Air.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.popularmechanics.com/cars/reviews/drives/2012-honda-cr-v-test-drive-6563613?click=main_sr#fbIndex1" target="_blank">2012 Honda CR-V</a>: A sharp looking, very versatile and practical car that’s fun to drive.</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Marriage Moment: Getting Lucky and Date Nights</strong></h2>
<p>Valentine’s Day is less than a month away. Before you groan, think about using this as an opportunity to “pursue” your wife … you know, like you did when you were first dating. You may say, “But I’ve already won her; it’s hard to get excited about pursuing her.”  But in her heart, she doesn’t want to be taken for granted; she wants to be pursued by her lover.</p>
<p>And there is at least one thing our wives can inspire pursuit from most of us guys …. Jesse so far has read one-third of the latest issue of <em><a href="http://www.rebelmagazine.com/" target="_blank">Rebel Magazine</a></em><em>. </em>His key take-away so far is this sentence written by Ashlan Gorse: “I love when a man cooks for me, and if he cleans up after, he’s definitely getting lucky.”</p>
<p>The latest issue of <em>Thriving Family Magazine</em> shares eight fun ideas for <a href="http://www.thrivingfamily.com/Features/Magazine/2012/date-night-ideas.aspx" target="_blank">low-cost dates</a> with your wife. If you these type of things to regularly “pursue” your wife, plus occasionally splurge on her, it’s a pretty good bet that she’ll make sure you get lucky. Isn’t it awfully nice when she’s the one to initiate “getting it on”? That frequent scenario is worth pursuing!</p>
<h2><strong>SportsMan: Road to the Super Bowl</strong></h2>
<p>The San Francisco 49ers beat the New Orleans Saints in a very exciting and surprising game. Even more surprising, the Packers lost at home by 17 points to the Giants. Tim Tebow’s Broncos lost to the Patriots, and Houston lost to the Baltimore Ravens. The SportsMan Ty Daniels shares his predictions for this weekend’s final-four games.</p>
<p>Don’t miss next week’s show, when we’ll feature Dr. Jim Sharon, the author of <em>Ordinary Men, Extraordinary Lives</em>.</p>
