		<description><![CDATA[Tom Cruise returns for the fourth time to the Mission: Impossible franchise. This time, everything seems to goes wrong as Ethan Hunt and his new team go rogue in an attempt to prevent nuclear war after the Kremlin is bombed. Listen in to hear why Jesse and J. J. decided to give this surprisingly funny [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><img class="wp-image-376 alignleft" title="Tom Cruise climbing building in Mission: Impossible - Ghost Protocol" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/mi4-4-202x300.jpg" alt="Tom Cruise climbing building in Mission: Impossible - Ghost Protocol" width="149" height="221" /></p>
<p>Tom Cruise returns for the fourth time to the <em>Mission: Impossible</em> franchise. This time, everything seems to goes wrong as Ethan Hunt and his new team go rogue in an attempt to prevent nuclear war after the Kremlin is bombed. Listen in to hear why Jesse and J. J. decided to give this surprisingly funny action thriller 5 stars. Jeremy Renner, Simon Pegg, and Paula Patton also star in this near-perfect movie.</p>
<p>NOTE: One of the things that makes this movie so cool is that Tom Cruise does his own stunts, and in the scene in the picture here, when he climbs up the side of the Burj Khalifa &#8211; at over a half-mile tall, it&#8217;s the tallest building in the world &#8211; he really did climb up it! (It was not CG!)</p>
