		<item>
		<title>MCR-009: The Resolutions Revolution</title>
		<link>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-009-taking-control-of-the-new-year/</link>
		<comments>http://www.mancaveradio.com/mcr-009-taking-control-of-the-new-year/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Jan 2012 18:37:30 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cave@mancaveradio.com (Jesse and J. J. Lahey)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=358</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Society for Prevention of Failed New Year’s Resolutions. 5 Resolutions in 5 Days. Taking Control of the New Year: four simple points to help you make 2012 a year to remember. SportsMan covers the bowl games. Man Hero: Lt. Jason Redman Society for Prevention of Failed New Year’s Resolutions Many people have already given up [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><em><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/iStock_000014926475XSmall.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-359" title="New Year's Resolutions" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/iStock_000014926475XSmall.jpg" alt="New Year's Resolutions" width="293" height="410" /></a>Society for Prevention of Failed New Year’s Resolutions. 5 Resolutions in 5 Days. Taking Control of the New Year: four simple points to help you make 2012 a year to remember. SportsMan covers the bowl games. Man Hero: Lt. Jason Redman</em></p>
<h2><strong>Society for Prevention of Failed New Year’s Resolutions</strong></h2>
<p>Many people have already given up on their 2012 resolutions, but Jesse and JJ haven’t even set resolutions! They are excited about the plans they’re shaping up for the year, though, including several triathlons and half-marathons.</p>
<h2><strong>5 Resolutions in 5 Days</strong></h2>
<p>The guys take a call from Jimmy, who has already completed the five resolutions he set for the new year: Lose 20 pounds, watch every Schwarzenegger film, get a Master’s degree, find a cure for a major disease, and grow a ponytail. How did he accomplish all five in just the first five days of 2012, and what will he do for the rest of the year?</p>
<h2><strong>Taking Control of the New Year</strong></h2>
<p>What would make 2012 a great year for you? It’s not too late to set a few goals that you can get excited about – even if you’ve already given up on any resolutions that you’d already set! The guys share four simple points to help you make 2012 a year to remember, based on an article by <a href="http://goodpeoplegoodbusiness.areavoices.com/2011/12/28/take-control-of-your-life-and-resolutions/ " target="_blank">The Village Business Institute</a>.</p>
<h2><strong>SportsMan</strong></h2>
<p>Ty ventures outside to run despite 6-degree windchill. Jesse has been focusing more on indoor workouts. He’s trying out CrossFit.com and likes it so far. It’s a free website that posts workouts every day, providing a good mix of cardio plus strength-training. Jesse likes that these intense workouts take only about 20 minutes, with plenty of variety to prevent stagnation.</p>
<p>College football bowl games are in full swing, with many lopsided games but also some great matchups. In fact, so far, five bowls have gone into overtime – including the Sugar Bowl (Michigan beat Virginia Tech), and the Outback Bowl (Michigan State beat Georgia in triple overtime). Ohio State ended the year with seven losses, their worst record since 1897 – more than 110 years ago!</p>
<p>Ty predicts Alabama will win the National Championship game over LSU, despite the fact that LSU won earlier in the season when these same teams faced each other.</p>
<p>This coming weekend is the NFL’s Wildcard Weekend, kicking off the playoffs and setting the stage for the Super Bowl.</p>
<h2><strong><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Lt.-Jason-Redmans-Sign-to-All.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-360" title="Lt.-Jason-Redmans-Sign-to-All" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Lt.-Jason-Redmans-Sign-to-All.jpg" alt="" width="253" height="300" /></a>Man Hero: Lt. Jason Redman</strong></h2>
<p>We couldn’t help but be amazed by the sign posted on the hospital door of a severely wounded soldier: “The wounds I received, I got in a job I love, doing it for people I love, supporting the freedom of a country I deeply love.”</p>
<p>Navy SEAL Lt. Jason Redman isn’t just tough; he has a great attitude plus compassion for others. Jason Redman joined the Navy in 1992, and rose from the ranks of enlisted soldiers to become an officer. And when life literally knocked him down (on a mission in Iraq, his face was shattered when he would shot in the head and arm), he got back up and continued to make a difference. He went on to start a non-profit organization called <a href="http://www.woundedwear.org/Wounded_Wear_New/Wounded_Wear_Home.html" target="_blank">Wounded Wear</a>, to help other wounded soldiers recover.</p>
<p>An interview featuring Jason and his wife, who together have three children, is here: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xImRz5aBO6k" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xImRz5aBO6k</a></p>
