		<title>MCR-008: Man Cave Christmas Carol</title>
		<link>http://www.mancaveradio.com/dec-21-2011-man-cave-radio/</link>
		<comments>http://www.mancaveradio.com/dec-21-2011-man-cave-radio/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 21 Dec 2011 17:51:21 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cave@mancaveradio.com (Jesse and J. J. Lahey)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=343</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[A special Christmas edition of Man Cave Radio, featuring a special appearance by Mr. Christmas Carol himself, Charles Dickens! Man Toys: JetLev Water-Powered Jetpack. Man Cave Movies review of Sherlock Holmes, A Game of Shadows. SportsMan: this week’s game-changers in the NFL. Man Hero: George Washington, every-day guy. Wimpmakers: video games and medicating kids. Man [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><em><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/ChristmasPicture.jpg"><img class="alignright  wp-image-344" title="Christmas tree decorated with red and gold " src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/ChristmasPicture.jpg" alt="Christmas tree decorated with red and gold " width="175" height="263" /></a>A special Christmas edition of Man Cave Radio, featuring a special appearance by Mr. Christmas Carol himself, Charles Dickens! Man Toys: JetLev Water-Powered Jetpack. Man Cave Movies review of Sherlock Holmes, A Game of Shadows. SportsMan: this week’s game-changers in the NFL. Man Hero: George Washington, every-day guy. Wimpmakers: video games and medicating kids.</em></p>
<h2>Man Toys</h2>
<p>The latest edition of Popular Mechanics is out – and woohoo! – it features a jetpack that the average guy could have a chance to fly sometime soon. Sure, it’s a water jetpack and not the rocket-fuel jetpack that James Bond flew in <em>Thunderball</em>, but it looks like a ton of run. Check the video of the <a href="http://www.popularmechanics.com/outdoors/sports/watersports/jetlev-water-powered-jetpack-test-flight-exclusive-video-5525115" target="_blank">JetLev Water-Powered Jetpack Test Flight</a>.</p>
<h2><strong>Man Cave Movies</strong></h2>
<p>The guys provide their review of <em>Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows</em>, the 2011 follow-up to the 2009 hit reboot of stories about the world’s most famous detective. Robert Downey, Jr. and Jude Law resume their roles as Holmes and Dr. Watson, taking on the diabolical Professor Moriarty (Jared Harris).</p>
<h2><strong>SportsMan</strong></h2>
<p>What the heck happened this week? Tim Tebow’s winning streak is broken … a heart-breaking loss crushes the Packers dreams of finally breaking the curse of the 1972 Dolphins … and the Colts finally win a game. Featuring Ty Daniels, the SportsMan (not dead yet).</p>
<h2><strong>Man Hero: George Washington, Every-Day Guy</strong></h2>
<p>Like most Americans, Jesse used to think of George Washington as a guy famous for being our first president. After reading <em>Killing Lincoln </em>on his Kindle, though, Jesse saw the suggested book <em>Being George Washington</em> by Glenn Beck. While some parts of the book dragged, and other parts skipped around so much chronologically that it became hard to follow, certain chapters were very exciting and inspiring. This was an every-day joe, a “man’s man” who – long before he became president &#8212; became the most famous American of his time by showing courage, honesty, and self-sacrifice in both big and little moments of life.</p>
<h2><strong>Wimpmakers</strong></h2>
<p>Can over-use of video games, texting, and touch-screens lead to symptoms similar to bipolar disorder? Can poor sleep habits, poor nutrition, and other factors lead to symptoms similar to ADHD? If so, what happens when doctors want to put you or your kids on long-term medications to manage these symptoms? It sounds like the potential for a generation of unhappy, unproductive wimps.</p>
<p>This discussion is based on information from:</p>
<ul>
<li>Talk given in October 25, 2011 by Anthony J. Siegel, M.D. (University of Kentucky’s Director of Medical Student Education, Associate Professor of Psychiatry, and Outpatient Adult Psychiatrist).</li>
<li><a href="http://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/mental-wealth/201106/misdiagnosed-bipolar-disorder-is-all-the-rage" target="blank">“Misdiagnosed? Bipolar Disorder is All the Rage!” by <em>Victoria L. Dunckley, M.D., Psychology Today, 6/7/2011. </em></a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.webmd.com/add-adhd/news/20110919/kids-poor-bedtime-habits-may-bring-adhd-misdiagnosis" target="_blank">“Kids&#8217; Poor Bedtime Habits May Bring ADHD Misdiagnosis,” by Daniel J. DeNoon, <em>WebMD Health News</em>, Sept. 20, 2011.</a></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Guys’ Guide to Christmas Shopping</strong></h2>
<p>It’s December 21st, a little early for Christmas shopping in your book, but it’s time to at least start thinking about what you might want to get the loved ones in your life this holiday season. Of course, you won’t actually buy the gifts until Christmas Eve, but it’s a good idea to decide what you should get everybody. Here are five rules that should help you avoid screwing it all up.</p>
<h2><strong>Man Cave Christmas Carol</strong></h2>
<p>For this week’s Men at Work segment, Jesse Scrooge attempts to interview Mr. Christmas Carol himself, Charles Dickens. Instead, his co-host J. J. Cratchitt takes over the show, and a series of ghosts – er, spirits – descend on Jesse to persuade him to change his evil ways. Special appearance by Zach Lahey as Turkey Boy.</p>
<div class="shr-publisher-343"></div><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><div class='shareaholic-like-buttonset' style='float:none;height:30px;'><a class='shareaholic-fblike' data-shr_layout='button_count' data-shr_showfaces='false' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fdec-21-2011-man-cave-radio%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-008%3A+Man+Cave+Christmas+Carol'></a><a class='shareaholic-googleplusone' data-shr_size='medium' data-shr_count='true' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fdec-21-2011-man-cave-radio%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-008%3A+Man+Cave+Christmas+Carol'></a><a class='shareaholic-tweetbutton' data-shr_count='horizontal' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fdec-21-2011-man-cave-radio%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-008%3A+Man+Cave+Christmas+Carol'></a></div><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?a=YQcEL-bP5Eo:8HWYBJVUSWE:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?a=YQcEL-bP5Eo:8HWYBJVUSWE:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/mancaveradio?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></img></a>
</div>]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.mancaveradio.com/dec-21-2011-man-cave-radio/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>

		<itunes:subtitle>A special Christmas edition of Man Cave Radio, featuring a special appearance by Mr. Christmas Carol himself, Charles Dickens! Man Toys: JetLev Water-Powered Jetpack. Man Cave Movies review of Sherlock Holmes, A Game of Shadows.</itunes:subtitle>
		<itunes:summary>A special Christmas edition of Man Cave Radio, featuring a special appearance by Mr. Christmas Carol himself, Charles Dickens! Man Toys: JetLev Water-Powered Jetpack. Man Cave Movies review of Sherlock Holmes, A Game of Shadows. SportsMan: this week’s game-changers in the NFL. Man Hero: George Washington, every-day guy. Wimpmakers: video games and medicating kids.
Man Toys
The latest edition of Popular Mechanics is out – and woohoo! – it features a jetpack that the average guy could have a chance to fly sometime soon. Sure, it’s a water jetpack and not the rocket-fuel jetpack that James Bond flew in Thunderball, but it looks like a ton of run. Check the video of the JetLev Water-Powered Jetpack Test Flight.
Man Cave Movies
The guys provide their review of Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows, the 2011 follow-up to the 2009 hit reboot of stories about the world’s most famous detective. Robert Downey, Jr. and Jude Law resume their roles as Holmes and Dr. Watson, taking on the diabolical Professor Moriarty (Jared Harris).
SportsMan
What the heck happened this week? Tim Tebow’s winning streak is broken … a heart-breaking loss crushes the Packers dreams of finally breaking the curse of the 1972 Dolphins … and the Colts finally win a game. Featuring Ty Daniels, the SportsMan (not dead yet).
Man Hero: George Washington, Every-Day Guy
Like most Americans, Jesse used to think of George Washington as a guy famous for being our first president. After reading Killing Lincoln on his Kindle, though, Jesse saw the suggested book Being George Washington by Glenn Beck. While some parts of the book dragged, and other parts skipped around so much chronologically that it became hard to follow, certain chapters were very exciting and inspiring. This was an every-day joe, a “man’s man” who – long before he became president -- became the most famous American of his time by showing courage, honesty, and self-sacrifice in both big and little moments of life.
Wimpmakers
Can over-use of video games, texting, and touch-screens lead to symptoms similar to bipolar disorder? Can poor sleep habits, poor nutrition, and other factors lead to symptoms similar to ADHD? If so, what happens when doctors want to put you or your kids on long-term medications to manage these symptoms? It sounds like the potential for a generation of unhappy, unproductive wimps.

This discussion is based on information from:

	Talk given in October 25, 2011 by Anthony J. Siegel, M.D. (University of Kentucky’s Director of Medical Student Education, Associate Professor of Psychiatry, and Outpatient Adult Psychiatrist).
	“Misdiagnosed? Bipolar Disorder is All the Rage!” by Victoria L. Dunckley, M.D., Psychology Today, 6/7/2011. 
	“Kids' Poor Bedtime Habits May Bring ADHD Misdiagnosis,” by Daniel J. DeNoon, WebMD Health News, Sept. 20, 2011.

Guys’ Guide to Christmas Shopping
It’s December 21st, a little early for Christmas shopping in your book, but it’s time to at least start thinking about what you might want to get the loved ones in your life this holiday season. Of course, you won’t actually buy the gifts until Christmas Eve, but it’s a good idea to decide what you should get everybody. Here are five rules that should help you avoid screwing it all up.
Man Cave Christmas Carol
For this week’s Men at Work segment, Jesse Scrooge attempts to interview Mr. Christmas Carol himself, Charles Dickens. Instead, his co-host J. J. Cratchitt takes over the show, and a series of ghosts – er, spirits – descend on Jesse to persuade him to change his evil ways. Special appearance by Zach Lahey as Turkey Boy.</itunes:summary>
