		<itunes:subtitle>Interview with Dan Miller, author of the widely acclaimed books 48 Days To The Work You Love and No More Mondays. “Man movies” we most look forward to in 2012. SportsMan: Tiger Woods gets a win after a two-year drought, plus a look at the Indy Colts,</itunes:subtitle>
		<itunes:summary>Interview with Dan Miller, author of the widely acclaimed books 48 Days To The Work You Love and No More Mondays. “Man movies” we most look forward to in 2012. SportsMan: Tiger Woods gets a win after a two-year drought, plus a look at the Indy Colts, what’s wrong with NASCAR, and why cagefighting is actually pretty cool. Tony Elam returns from the brink of financial ruin. Interview with Man Cave Radio co-host J. J. Lahey. UberMan breaks a two-week slump … and writer’s block.
Public Service Announcement
By the request of the Society for the Prevention of Ill Manners, J. J. shares the top 5 Ways to Tick People Off.
Man Movies to Watch for in 2012
Fresh from watching “Captain America” and “Thor” this week on DVD, the guys tell why their most-anticipated movies of 2012 are “The Avengers,” “Spiderman 4,” “Wrath of the Titans,” “Men in Black 3,” “Bourne Legacy,” – and potentially the biggest movie of next year: “The Dark Knight Rises.”
SportsMan
Tiger Woods finally gets a win after a two-year drought. What’s up with the Colts … they won the Super Bowl two years ago, but this year they can’t win a single game? And what’s up with NASCAR … it’s no fun to watch any more? Also, Jesse discovers that cage-fighting is actually pretty cool … and so is karate, for that matter. He’s always been a lover (not a fighter); so why the new interest in martial arts?
Men At Work
 Dan Miller talks about what it’s like to be an author. If you write a book that thousands of people buy, are you set for life?
Wide World of Writing
Through the magic of the Internet, J. J. is transported to Tennessee, where he’s been invited to join a very good crowd that has turned out to watch local boy Dan Miller write his new book, which has the working title Wisdom Meets Passion: Where Generations Collide and Collaborate At Work. Get carried away with the audience as Dan writes the very first sentence!
Winning At Work
Last week on Man Cave Radio, Tony Elam shared what he had learned about work and life after several years as a hotel bellman. This week, he shares the rest of his story, how he “failed at mediocrity” and experienced financial ruin … but came back from the brink to find forward motion for himself and others. http://findingforwardmotion.com.
Interview in Tennessee
While waiting for Dan Miller to return from Half Time, J. J. interviews a famous radio star.
UberMan
UberMan breaks a two-week slump … and conquers writer’s block. Now, will Frog Boy become his sidekick?</itunes:summary>
