				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=218</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Interview with Chad Jeffers, guitarist and songwriter. Experiments in making college affordable. The gun makes the hunter? International Men’s Day 2011. Don’t countrify my marriage. Expectations make the man. Juggling all the balls. UberMan: The Man, The Musician, The Legend. Experiments in Making College Affordable Although only age 16, J. J. is experimenting with three ways [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p><em><a href="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Chad-Jeffers.jpeg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-227" style="margin-left: 15px; margin-right: 15px;" title="Chad Jeffers" src="http://www.mancaveradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Chad-Jeffers-300x220.jpg" alt="Chad Jeffers" width="219" height="160" /></a>Interview with Chad Jeffers, guitarist and songwriter. Experiments in making college affordable. The gun makes the hunter? International Men’s Day 2011. Don’t countrify my marriage. Expectations make the man. Juggling all the balls. UberMan: The Man, The Musician, The Legend.</em></p>
<h2><strong>Experiments in Making College Affordable</strong></h2>
<p>Although only age 16, J. J. is experimenting with three ways to get college credit … on-site class at local community college, online class, and independent study for a <a href="http://clep.collegeboard.org" target="_blank">CLEP exam</a>. Inspired by <em>College without </em>Compromise, by Scott &amp; Kris Wightman.</p>
<h2><strong>The Gun Makes the Hunter?</strong></h2>
<p>Steve Hanley says that with his new gun, he’s actually hitting his target once in a while.</p>
<h2><strong>International Men’s Day</strong></h2>
<p>International Men’s Day is now observed and celebrated in over 60 countries. For more information, including an overview of goals and focus for the 2011 event as well as some great short video clips of everyday men from around world sharing their thoughts on the day, visit the <a href="http://www.internationalmensday.com" target="_blank">International Men’s Day website</a>.</p>
<h2><strong>Don’t Countrify My Marriage</strong></h2>
<p>Jesse demonstrates the risk that writing country songs can bring to marriage.</p>
<h2><strong>Expectations Make the Man</strong></h2>
<p>Comments on an intriguing <a href="http://authorrickjohnson.blogspot.com" target="_blank">post</a> by Rick Johnson, founder of Better Dads, author of several books. Rick says, &#8220;The rule of thumb in the business world is that employees are only capable at best of living up to about 75% of the expectations that an employer has for them.&#8221;</p>
<h2><strong>Men At Work</strong></h2>
<p><a href="http://www.chadjeffers.com " target="_blank">Chad Jeffers</a>, highly-respected slide guitarist, has traveled the globe with high profile acts including Keith Urban, Carrie Underwood, Kenny Loggins, and his own band, Pinmonkey.</p>
<h2><strong>Juggling All the Balls</strong></h2>
<p>Imagine life is a game in which you are juggling five balls. The balls are called work, family, health, friends, and integrity. And you&#8217;re keeping all of them in the air. But one day you finally come to understand that work is a rubber ball. If you drop it, it will bounce back. The other four balls–family, health, friends, integrity–are made of glass. If you drop one of these, it will be irrevocably scuffed, nicked, perhaps even shattered. And once you truly understand the lesson of the five balls, you will have the beginnings of balance in your life. &#8211; <a href="http://www.jamespatterson.com/about_contact.php" target="_blank">James Patterson</a>, <em>Suzanne&#8217;s Diary for Nicholas</em>.</p>
<h2><strong>Our First Caller!</strong></h2>
<p>Kip can’t wait for Thanksgiving turkey. We wonder he exemplifies the intelligence and personality of our listening audience.</p>
<h2><strong>Sign of Wisdom</strong></h2>
<p>The most manifest sign of wisdom is a continual cheerfulness. – Michel de Montaigne (Writer, philosopher and statement from the French Renaissance</p>
<p>Saxophone and voice by Joel Sheltrown, performing last night at the Kiwanis Variety Show in West Branch, Mi.</p>
<p>You can listen to Dan Miller’s weekly “48 Days to the Work You Love” podcast at <a href="http://www.48days.com" target="_blank">www.48days.com</a>.</p>
<p>The formula E + R = O is from speaker and author Kent Julian (<a href="http://www.kentjulian.com/">www.kentjulian.com</a> and <a href="http://www.liveitforward.com/">www.liveitforward.com</a>).</p>
<h2><strong>UberMan: The Man, The Musician, The Legend</strong></h2>
<p>UberMan’s songwriting career is interrupted – we hope forever – by an urgent situation. Is this his first opportunity to actually rescue someone?</p>
<div class="shr-publisher-218"></div><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><div class='shareaholic-like-buttonset' style='float:none;height:30px;'><a class='shareaholic-fblike' data-shr_layout='button_count' data-shr_showfaces='false' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fnov-19-2011-man-cave-radio%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-003%3A+International+Men%27s+Day'></a><a class='shareaholic-googleplusone' data-shr_size='medium' data-shr_count='true' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fnov-19-2011-man-cave-radio%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-003%3A+International+Men%27s+Day'></a><a class='shareaholic-tweetbutton' data-shr_count='horizontal' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fnov-19-2011-man-cave-radio%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-003%3A+International+Men%27s+Day'></a></div><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div class="feedflare">
