		<title>MCR-002: Think of Yourself As an Athlete</title>
		<link>http://www.mancaveradio.com/nov-9-2011-man-cave-radio/</link>
		<comments>http://www.mancaveradio.com/nov-9-2011-man-cave-radio/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 15 Nov 2011 23:15:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>cave@mancaveradio.com (Jesse and J. J. Lahey)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Listen to the Show]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mancaveradio.com/?p=150</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Man Toys for iGeeks Jesse gets geeked up about his new iPhone 4S. And in the aftermath of yet another (and hopefully the last) Windows disappointment for the Lahey gang, Jesse and JJ talk about their efforts to interest Erin in the iPad 2. Too Old to Become Mr. Stud Athlete? Two years ago, Marty [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><h2><strong>Man Toys for iGeeks</strong></h2>
<p>Jesse gets geeked up about his new iPhone 4S. And in the aftermath of yet another (and hopefully the last) Windows disappointment for the Lahey gang, Jesse and JJ talk about their efforts to interest Erin in the iPad 2.</p>
<h2><strong>Too Old to Become Mr. Stud Athlete?</strong></h2>
<p>Two years ago, Marty couldn’t run a mile. This past week, he signs up at the last minute to run his first half-marathon. But at 59 years old, can he finish the race? Is 59 too old to start a new sport? Jesse joins him on the 13-mile run in case the old coot needs to be rescued.</p>
<p>Jesse continues to live out a key message from a speech he heard nearly 10 years ago called “Think of Yourself As an Athlete,” by former Stanford and pro basketball player Mariah Burton Nelson (<a href="http://www.mariahburtonnelson.com" target="_blank">mariahburtonnelson.com</a>).</p>
<h2><strong>Men at Work</strong></h2>
<p>Jeff McManus (<a href="http://www.plantingtogrow.com/" target="_blank">plantingtogrow.com</a>) gets paid to play with big toys. As Director of Landscaping at The University of Mississippi, he leads a team that creates the “wow factor” that helps Ole Miss attract the best and brightest students. His role is important because 62% of incoming freshmen make their decision to attend a given school based on their experience in the first 15 minutes they spend on campus &#8212; impressions and experience within their first 15 minutes on campus.</p>
<h2><strong>Gotta Love a Woman in a Tool Belt</strong></h2>
<p>Jesse ventures out of the Man Cave to demonstrate the payoff for a guy in showing support and enthusiasm for your wife’s interests. We weren’t sure what Erin would call her latest project (Woman Cave? Mom Cave?) … but the first name that popped into her head was “Girl Cave.”</p>
<h2><strong>The Best Sex Book I Never Read</strong></h2>
<p>Jesse talks about how many years ago, his life was changed simply by hearing the title of a book by Dr. Kevin Leman. Our Quote of the Week is from that book title: <em>Sex Begins in the Kitchen</em>.</p>
<h2><strong>Winning with Your Kids</strong></h2>
<p>Jesse shares a point to help guys raise kids that don’t drive you crazy.</p>
<h2><strong>Winning at Work</strong></h2>
<p>What do Steve Jobs, the “glass ceiling,” and Generation X have in common … and what difference does it make in how guys can succeed on the job?</p>
<h2><strong>UberMan: F-Word Frenzy</strong></h2>
<p>UberMan is introduced to the new villain The Jesster, and he has a few choice words to say on the matter. Meanwhile, his alter-ego Michael Buckminster tackles landscaping at a large university.</p>
<div class="shr-publisher-150"></div><!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><div class='shareaholic-like-buttonset' style='float:none;height:30px;'><a class='shareaholic-fblike' data-shr_layout='button_count' data-shr_showfaces='false' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fnov-9-2011-man-cave-radio%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-002%3A+Think+of+Yourself+As+an+Athlete'></a><a class='shareaholic-googleplusone' data-shr_size='medium' data-shr_count='true' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fnov-9-2011-man-cave-radio%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-002%3A+Think+of+Yourself+As+an+Athlete'></a><a class='shareaholic-tweetbutton' data-shr_count='horizontal' data-shr_href='http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mancaveradio.com%2Fnov-9-2011-man-cave-radio%2F' data-shr_title='MCR-002%3A+Think+of+Yourself+As+an+Athlete'></a></div><div style="clear: both; min-height: 1px; height: 3px; width: 100%;"></div><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetBottom Automatic --><div class="feedflare">
