		<itunes:summary>Our second pre-launch show! The first recording on our new audio equipment! Many thanks to Cliff Ravenscraft from podcastanswerman.com for getting me this far. Also thanks to Erin, J. J., and my other kids for setting up the studio while I was out of town.

Here are the topics covered in this episode:

The first print issue of the brand-new magazine Rebel arrived this week. See www.rebelmagazine.com

Jesse practically wet himself when he discovered the man stuff in the April 2011 issue of Popular Mechanics. See www.popularmechanics.com

Man Cave One is now coming together! This space used to hold my weightlifting equipment, but this week J. J. moved all that to a section of the basement. I now have a real space, next to my office, that is just for me. It’s dedicated to two things … mostly for me relaxing, but also to record our new radio show.

We are looking forward to the movie Courageus, which opens this weekend. Jesse has read the novelized version, and provides a mixed review here. Based on the progressing production quality of the producers’ prior movies – Flywheel, Facing the Giants, and Fireproof – we are nonetheless fairly confident that the new movie will be worth watching. Hopefully, though, they will learn the value of artistic subtlety. See http://www.courageousthemovie.com

For our “Men at Work” feature, I interviewed Ron Oliver, a CNC operator at Prescott Products. See www.prescottproducts.com

After the show, we agreed that we sucked, but not nearly so bad as we did in June. A couple of the lowpoints:
• Jesse can’t seem to talk to his co-host or guest and speak directly into the mic at the same time. And despite Ron being a great guest, Jesse can’t think of anything to say except “Um.”
• J. J. gives away the punch line to Jesse’s story from When Character Was King by Peggy Noonan.

Once launched, our actual show will be much more fun and faster-paced. Right now we are still working on a lot of the behind-the-scenes details for the show, so we didn’t put any planning or preparation into the show itself.</itunes:summary>
